==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Labrum
<hw>La"brum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Labra</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Labrums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A lip or edge, as of a basin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An organ in insects
and crustaceans covering the upper part of the mouth, and serving as an
upper lip. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Hymenoptera</er>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The external margin of the aperture of a shell. See
<er>Univalve</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Labrus</ent>⟦br⟧
